sub_title: Associate Professor University of Twente and Universidad de Chile
summary:
Associate Professor of Civil Engineering at University of Twente, the Netherlands, and at Universidad de Chile.
Civil Engineer and MSc in Transport Engineering, Universidad de Chile (2007).
PhD, Institute of Transport and Logistics Studies (ITLS), The University of Sydney, Australia (2012). 
Recipient of a Humboldt Fellowship for Experienced Researchers, TU Munich, Germany (2019-2020). 

My main research interests are the design, planning and operation of public transport systems in multimodal settings and the study of emerging mobility technologies from a sustainable mobility perspective. I have worked on transport research projects in Chile, Australia, Singapore, Germany and the Netherlands. Invited several times as specialist to give presentations to the Transport Commission of the Lower House and the Senate in Chile, over bills under discussion concerning public transport subsidies, ride-hailing platforms, traffic safety and fare evasion in public transport. I have served in the Experts Panel of Chile’s Ministry of Social Development, for the analysis of improvements to the methodology of cost-benefit assessment for transport projects, in the Experts Panel of the Ministry of Transport to improve the understanding of fare evasion in Santiago’s public transport and in the Experts Panel of the government’s MAPS Initiative (Mitigation of Climate Change and Low Carbon Development).

Google Scholar Profile: https://scholar.google.com.au/citations?user=gi4wZsMAAAAJ&hl=en
